<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/apple-card/">Apple Card</a> users can get extra Daily Cash back when shopping at Ace Hardware this holiday season. Apple and Ace are offering five percent Daily Cash back on up to &#36;500 in <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/apple-pay/">Apple Pay</a> purchases, for a total of &#36;25.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/11/apple-card-promo-ace-hardware-daily-cash.jpg" alt="" width="1340" height="754" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1027436" /><br/>
Ace Hardware is an &zwnj;Apple Card&zwnj; partner that normally provides three percent Daily Cash back on &zwnj;Apple Pay&zwnj; purchases made with the &zwnj;Apple Card&zwnj;, but the promotion offers an additional two percent. The deal will be in place through December 15. <br/>
<br/>
Getting the cash back reward requires Ace customers to use &zwnj;Apple Pay&zwnj; with the &zwnj;Apple Card&zwnj; either online, in the Ace Hardware app, or in retail store locations. <br/>
<br/>
Apple is also currently offering five percent Daily Cash back for up to &#36;500 in purchases made at Booking.com. <br/>
<br/>
